quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  16,41,"And as to those who when oppressed have fled their country for the sake of God, we will surely provide them a goodly abode in this world, but greater the reward of the next life, did they but know it"
  16,42,They who bear ills with patience and put their trust in the Lord
  16,43,"None have we sent before thee but men inspired ask of those who have Books of Monition, if ye know it not"
  16,44,"With proofs of their mission and Scriptures: and to thee have we sent down this Book of Monition that thou mayest make clear to men what hath been sent down to them, and that they may ponder it"
  16,45,"What! Are they then who have plotted mischiefs, sure that God will not cause the earth to cleave under them? or that a chastisement will not come upon them whence they looked not for it"
  16,46,"Or that He will not seize upon them in their comings and goings, while they shall not be able to resist him"
  16,47,"Or that he will not seize them with some slowly wasting scourge? But verily your Lord is Good, Gracious"
  16,48,"Have they not seen how everything which God hath created turneth its shadow right and left, prostrating itself before God in all abasement"
  16,49,"And all in the Heavens and all on the Earth, each thing that moveth, and the very angels, prostrate them in adoration before God, and are free from pride"
  16,50,"They fear their Lord who is above them, and do what they are bidden"